<subSubSection id="DA74A2E5E268B508D35B502636D6CE6D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0C2CFBA4449E1EF5BED274DDBFC540F1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A012E0F849AD82DA9BC7296FB7751AFB" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Body length: male: 8 mm (female unknown). A sturdy, entirely black species without pale wing markings, without golden pile on thorax or abdomen, with a produced vertex. Male genitalia as in 
<figureCitation id="16E3CFE915D573DBA1A01EE5F4BB28DC" captionStart="Figures 262–267" captionStartId="F45" captionText="Figures 262 - 267. Male genitalia of Peradon species 262 P. hermetoides holotype 263 P. elongatus holotype 264 P. oligonax Colombia NHMUK 265 P. satyricus holotype 266 P. sciarus paratype 267 P. bidens Suriname RMNH." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.896.36493.figures262-267" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362315" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.896.36493.figures262-267">Fig. 265</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="716ED20314F425357EA71255C696A9F0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="F4DE744FD36BF2E1B6BFB2990C1DE22C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2003DF30C6608DCDB1ACE4C480A8FF35" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">In the specimen from Brazil the vertex is slightly less produced than in the type material, the median bulge on the face is somewhat less prominent, and the scutellar calcars are more or less straight (as opposed to curved and converging in the type specimens). The taxonomic value of these characters can only be assessed when further specimens become available.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="941CAA1A37A4445AC31A1EA2B6D1215F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="254301F760005355CC1D6FA55B0E147B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F9A36969CE47375634F89473D474A1D2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Known from the Brazilian state Amazonas, French Guiana, and Suriname.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
